++ Post-Incident Interviews with Project Gyakuten Team
[[/div]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Interviewer:** Where did Project Gyakuten come from?

**Dr. Panagiotopolous:** From the beginning of extradimensional operations, the Pataphysics Department has gotten glimpses of the narrative structure of our reality. We can observe several parallel narratives -- even before our narrative branch is born, the events of the future are already planned out. So we tried to stop all these events, but to no avail.

**Interviewer:** So Project Gyakuten is an attempt to stop those events from happening?

**Dr. Panagiotopolous:** Not just that. The goal of Project Gyakuten is to use the instability in the narrative for Foundation benefit. I just mentioned that we have no means of stopping these events, because they have been written and set in stone by the author. But outside of the narrative, we are able to control the narrative branches, and prevent further incidents from occurring in the future.
[[/div]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Interviewer:** What has the Department of Miscommunications done for the project?

**Dr. Forkley:** It's hard to understand, but we currently believe that SCP-CN-2626 lies within the field covered by the Department of Miscommunications. Though it does not affect our communication, the process by which information is transferred is ultimately based on SCP-CN-2626. Of course, we must not forget the Legal Department, established to deal with bureaucratic hazards; this department will do its job for Project Gyakuten. After all, reasoning is the weakest link of a narrative.
[[/div]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Interviewer:** What has the Department of Deduction done for the project?

**Dr. Veleafer:** We are all actors. We write stories, pretending that's what the authors think. But has Project Gyakuten really succeeded? I don't know. "Walking on the tip of a pen, seeking freedom in the absence of freedom" has always been the motto of the Department of Deduction, but we can question it: are we really able to achieve the freedom we seek?
[[/div]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
**Interviewer:** What has the Department of Logic done for the project?

**Dr. Henry:** The Department of Logic explores the relationship between logic and reality. You may have read that the Department of Logic was responsible for the logical rationalization work to ensure the continuation of the narrative we were influenced by.

**Dr. Henry:** But if you have the clearance to look at the archives of our department, you will see that we have explored the existence of the Moon, shaved the sun with Occam's Razor in more than one way. We are studying the blurred boundary of between subjective and objective reality. If my guesses are correct, the endpoint of the Department of Logic's research is, in the end, SCP-CN-2626. Our natural world is built atop the objective built from the subjective.
